"Even A Bouncer Can Cry," The New York Times City Room Blog, April 20, 2014. "An Elderly Litterbug," The New York Times City Room Blog, January 22, 2015. Gary Lippman (born August 8, 1963) is an American film producer, author, journalist, and attorney. Lippman's journalistic work has been published in The New York Times, The Paris Review, Vice, and more. He produced the film Vinyl in 2012, and his debut novel Set the Controls for the Heart of Sharon Tate was published by Rare Bird Books in 2019.